rComments: Great professor! Informative lectures; I learned a lot about archaeological landscapes. The assignments were reasonable in terms of difficulty and worth - I'd never even done some of these before, but still did well. Readings were provided online and were reasonable for each week. Clear explanation of expectations/exam/assignments and fair marker.
Banning is so passionate about what he does and it shows. He makes going to lectures worthwhile. Aswell, he always gives 110% to help us learn
A brilliant man who is very approachable and down to earth.  He cares about his students, I learned sooo much from him.
Very cool guy. He taught the course well, and I excelled. I especially loved the archaeology notebook assignments; a good idea, and really educational.
Very approchable, down to earth guy.  Tough with workload but easy going and funny as well.  Always cool when you can grab a beer with him after class.
somewhat interesting, a lot of theory very little history. Banning was very interested and knowledgeable, can be funny sometimes
As much as I was bored to death by the material, Prof. Banning was a great professor. He was funny and I liked listening to him.
He can be anal but he's really nice, interesting and knowledgable. Always has well organised and informative lectures on interesting topics.
interesting class...expectations of studnets isn't clear
I took all his courses.. this man rules!
